    Request objects for LAN operations. An AylaLanRequest contains a list of AylaLanCommands intended to be processed as a single operation.

    All AylaLanRequest objects return a LanResponse, which contains the list of completed commands that either have a response or an error returned. Each command holds its own response or error.

    When this request is processed in a queue that was initialized with an AylaLocalNetwork object, it will process each LAN command in order and gather the results. Even if each LAN command fails, the AylaLanRequest can still succeed, though each LanCommand contained within the request object will contain an error.

    The AylaLanRequest itself can fail if the device is not found or the LAN session is not running at the time the request is sent out.

    Generally, this request type is used internally and the results collated into a different type of response for an API. See AylaDevice.fetchPropertiesLAN(String[], Response.Listener, ErrorListener) for an example of this.
